Package grafioschtrader.repository

Interface GTNetInstrumentCurrencypairJpaRepository

All Superinterfaces:
org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair,Integer>, GTNetInstrumentCurrencypairJpaRepositoryCustom, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListCrudRepository<GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListPagingAndSortingRepository<GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.PagingAndSortingRepository<GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.query.QueryByExampleExecutor<GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair,Integer>
public interface GTNetInstrumentCurrencypairJpaRepository extends org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair,Integer>, GTNetInstrumentCurrencypairJpaRepositoryCustom
Repository for GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair entities. Provides access to currency pair instruments in the GTNet instrument pool, identified by from/to currency. For price data operations, use this repository to find instruments and then query GTNetLastpriceJpaRepository for the associated price data.

    • findLocalInstruments

      @Query(nativeQuery=true, value="SELECT g.* FROM gt_net_instrument_currencypair g\nJOIN currencypair c ON g.from_currency = c.from_currency AND g.to_currency = c.to_currency") List<GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair> findLocalInstruments()
      Finds all local currency pair instruments (those that exist in the local database). Uses a JOIN to determine locality dynamically based on matching from/to currencies.
      Returns:
      list of local currency pair instruments

    • findForeignInstruments

      @Query(nativeQuery=true, value="SELECT g.* FROM gt_net_instrument_currencypair g\nLEFT JOIN currencypair c ON g.from_currency = c.from_currency AND g.to_currency = c.to_currency\nWHERE c.id_securitycurrency IS NULL") List<GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair> findForeignInstruments()
      Finds all foreign currency pair instruments (those that do NOT exist in the local database). Uses a LEFT JOIN to find instruments with no matching local currency pair.
      Returns:
      list of foreign currency pair instruments

    • findByCurrencyPairKeys

      @Query("SELECT c FROM GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair c WHERE CONCAT(c.fromCurrency, \'|\', c.toCurrency) IN :keys") List<GTNetInstrumentCurrencypair> findByCurrencyPairKeys(@Param("keys") List<String> keys)
      Finds currency pair instruments by a list of composite keys (fromCurrency|toCurrency format). Used for batch lookups when matching instruments from GTNet requests.
      Parameters:
      keys - list of composite keys in "fromCurrency|toCurrency" format
      Returns:
      list of matching currency pair instruments

    • findLocalCurrencypairMappings

      @Query(nativeQuery=true, value="SELECT g.id_gt_net_instrument, c.id_securitycurrency\nFROM gt_net_instrument_currencypair g\nJOIN currencypair c ON g.from_currency = c.from_currency AND g.to_currency = c.to_currency\nWHERE g.id_gt_net_instrument IN (:ids)") List<Object[]> findLocalCurrencypairMappings(@Param("ids") List<Integer> instrumentIds)
      Determines which GTNet currency pair instruments have matching local currency pairs via JOIN. Returns mapping from GTNet instrument ID to local currencypair ID. Uses a native JOIN query to find local currency pairs that match the from/to currencies of the given GTNet instruments. This allows dynamic determination of instrument locality without storing the reference in the GTNetInstrument entity.
      Parameters:
      instrumentIds - list of GTNet instrument IDs to check for locality
      Returns:
      list of Object[] where [0] = idGtNetInstrument (Integer), [1] = idSecuritycurrency (Integer)
